The paper discusses the limitations of standard neural networks in learning abstract patterns based on identity rules, and proposes a new approach to modify neural network architectures. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), natural language processing (cs.CL), and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, with cs.LG being the most likely due to the focus on machine learning and neural networks.
